solution:
Because $200-96=104$ of those surveyed were male, $104-26=78$ of those surveyed are male listeners. [asy]
size(3inch, 1.5inch);
draw((0,0)--(7,0)--(7,2.5)--(0,2.5)--cycle);

label(scale(.75)*"Listen", (2.5, 2), N);
label(scale(.75)*"Don't Listen", (4.5, 2), N);
label(scale(.75)*"Total", (6.35, 2), N);
label(scale(.75)*"Male", (1, 1.33), N);
label(scale(.75)*"Female", (1, .66), N);
label(scale(.75)*"Total", (1, 0), N);
draw((1.75,0)--(1.75,2.5));
draw((3.25,0)--(3.25,2.5));
draw((5.75,0)--(5.75,2.5));
draw((0,.6)--(7,.6));
draw((0,1.2)--(7,1.2));
draw((0,1.8)--(7,1.8));
label(scale(.75)*"78", (2.5, 1.33), N, red);
label(scale(.75)*"58", (2.5, .66), N);
label(scale(.75)*"136", (2.5, 0), N);

label(scale(.75)*"26", (4.5, 1.33), N);
label(scale(.75)*"38", (4.5, .66), N, red);
label(scale(.75)*"64", (4.5, 0), N);

label(scale(.75)*"104", (6.35, 1.33), N, red);
label(scale(.75)*"96", (6.35, .66), N);
label(scale(.75)*"200", (6.35, 0), N);
[/asy] The percentage of males surveyed who listen to KAMC is $\frac{78}{104} \times 100\% =\boxed{75\%}$.

The $y$-intercept is $(0,c).$  Since this is the point closest to $(12,3),$ the line joining $(0,c)$ and $(12,3)$ is perpendicular to the tangent to the parabola at $(0,c).$

[asy]
unitsize(0.5 cm);

real parab (real x) {
  return(x^2 + 6*x + 5);
}

draw(graph(parab,-6.5,0.5),red);
draw((-7,0)--(15,0));
draw((0,-5)--(0,10));
draw(((0,5) + (5)*(1/6,1))--((0,5) + (-8)*(1/6,1)),dashed);
draw((0,5)--(12,3));

dot("$(12,3)$", (12,3), E);
dot("$(-5,0)$", (-5,0), SW);
dot("$(0,c)$", (0,5), W);
[/asy]

The equation of the tangent is of the form
\[y - c = mx\]for some real number $m,$ so $y = mx + c.$  Substituting into $y = x^2 + bx + c,$ we get
\[mx + c = x^2 + bx + c,\]so $x^2 + (b - m) x = 0.$  Since $y = mx + c$ is the equation of the tangent at $x = 0,$ this quadratic should have a double root of $x = 0,$ which means $m = b.$

Thus, the slope of the tangent is $b.$  The slope of the line joining $(0,c)$ and $(12,3)$ is $\frac{3 - c}{12},$ so
\[b \cdot \frac{3 - c}{12} = -1.\]Then $b = -\frac{12}{3 - c} = \frac{12}{c - 3}.$

Also, the parabola passes through $(-5,0),$ so
\[0 = 25 - 5b + c.\]Substituting $b = \frac{12}{c - 3},$ we get
\[25 - \frac{60}{c - 3} + c = 0.\]This simplifies to $c^2 + 22c - 135 = 0,$ which factors as $(c - 5)(c + 27) = 0.$  Hence, $c = 5$ or $c = -27.$

If $c = -27,$ then $b = -\frac{2}{5},$ which does not satisfy the given conditions.  Therefore, $c = 5,$ and $b = 6,$ so $(b,c) = \boxed{(6,5)}.$

Multiplying the given equation by $z - 1,$ we get
\[(z - 1)(z^7 + z^6 + z^5 + z^4 + z^3 + z^2 + z + 1) = 0,\]or $z^8 = 1.$  Thus, the vertices of $P$ are the eighth roots of unity, other than 1.

