Since the sum of the angles of a triangle is $180^\circ,$ $40^\circ+70^\circ+\angle 1=180^\circ$ and $\angle 1=70^\circ.$ This means that $\angle 2=110^\circ.$ Then $110^\circ+\angle 3+\angle
